Cole Reiner is a rising star in the world of professional rodeo, known for his exceptional skills in bareback riding. Born and raised in Kaycee, Wyoming, Reiner comes from a family of ranchers, including his parents Joe and Michelle Reiner. He also has a brother, whose name remains undisclosed.

Here you can follow Cole Reiner’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Cole Reiner 

Reiner’s passion for rodeo began at a young age, but it wasn’t until his teenage years that he convinced his father to let him ride saddle broncs. 

However, due to a mix-up with equipment, he ended up riding bareback horses instead, marking the start of his journey in this challenging rodeo event.

Early Career 

Reiner’s early career was marked by significant progress and success. He received a scholarship to attend college in Sheridan, Wyoming, where he honed his rodeo skills. 

His first professional paycheck came from a rodeo event in Bismarck, North Dakota, setting the stage for his rookie year in 2020.

Professional Career 

Cole Reiner is a professional rodeo contestant specializing in bareback riding. Born and raised in Buffalo, Wyoming, Reiner began his journey in rodeo during his college years, initially focusing on wrestling before transitioning to rodeo. His first professional paycheck came from a rodeo in Bismarck, North Dakota.

Reiner has had a successful career in rodeo, qualifying for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (NFR) four times. He has consistently placed high in the world standings, even reaching the top rank in bareback bronc riding.

In 2022, he earned a total of $228,021, with his career earnings amounting to $580,044 as of November 2023.

Throughout his career, Reiner has participated in over 40 rodeos annually, aiming to perform better at fewer rodeos to allow for recovery time.

Despite a knee injury that slowed him down, he managed to secure his fourth consecutive trip to the NFR. Some of his major regular season wins include the Texas Circuit Finals, the San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo, Rodeo Houston, and the Reno Rodeo.

Reiner’s strategy of participating in fewer rodeos but performing better in each has been successful, allowing him to earn enough money to stay in the top 15 and qualify for his fourth NFR. His goal for 2023 is to win a World Championship.

Cole Reiner’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Cole Reiner’s net worth is estimated to be around $1 million.

Career Earnings

Cole Reiner has had a successful career in professional rodeo, with his earnings reflecting his accomplishments in the sport. As of November 2023, his career earnings amount to $580,044. In 2022 alone, he earned a total of $228,021.

Throughout his career, Reiner has participated in over 40 rodeos annually, with some of his major regular season wins. These victories have contributed significantly to his earnings. For instance, in a span of about two weeks, he won nearly $35,000 and was sitting fourth in the world standings.

His earnings from the 2022 NFR amounted to $67,050. Reiner’s earnings have shown a steady increase over the years. For instance, his career earnings in 2021 were reported to be $344,511. His career earnings total around $154,325.

Personal Details

Girlfriend 

As of 2023, Cole Reiner is single and does not have a wife or girlfriend. He is currently focusing on his career.

How old is he?

Cole Reiner is approximately 24 years old as of 2023

How tall is he?

He stands around 170 cm tall.

What is his nationality?

His nationality is American.

FAQs About Cole Reiner

What is Cole Reiner’s main rodeo event?

Cole Reiner competes in the bareback riding event in rodeo.

What awards has he won in his rodeo career?

He was the PRCA | Resistol Rookie of the Year in bareback riding in 2020. He has also qualified for three straight Wrangler National Finals Rodeos.

What is his net worth in 2023?

As of 2023, his net worth is estimated to be around $1 million.
